review: Great team of  doctors, they were able to quickly do it üòä with utmost care and attention. Commendable service offered

To start with the experience.. i would go with the appearance of the hospital.. the moment you step into the hospital it gives you a premium feel and its super tidy.. all the staff are very well trained on how to manage and dis infecting the perimeters.. I had a few problems with my teeth and was in severe pain.. Dr sudhakar has given me a concrete plan and where to start.. he initially suggested me to go with Root canal .. i did get the root canal first sitting done with ease and no pain.. and when i went for the second sitting they have told me that extraction of the wisdom tooth is too important as the infection has passed to bone and it is severe.. thats when the mighty hands of Sudhakar took the play.. he was soo caring and so patient.. the moment i used to get pain he completely used to stop it and give a break.. the best part is i was forcing my self to withstand the pain but Dr Sudhakar was understanding that and he gave me all the time to relax.. he almost took 90 minutes to remove the wisdom tooth as it was way too complicated and the bone has grown around the tooth and my tooth was in sleeping position..  the best part of the surgery is i was expecting a huge lump or swelling on my face but trust me guys there was no swelling not even by a centimetre‚Ä¶ I have never seen any hospital placing a TV over your head so you can just watch the tv and enjoy while the doctors do their job ‚Äú this tv thought is legendary‚Äù i still have 1 more tooth extraction and 2 root canals to be done and i am not scared of going to a dentist anymore.. 
behind all of this execution and the treatment let me thank the silent hero of the hospital Dr Supraja.. I have never seen any doctor who take the initiative and call the patient and check with them as how they are and how is the healing process going on.. Thanks to you and your kind nature..
